
Paul smiled again and then opened the wicker basket. He pulled out a long bag and then took the bread out of it.
As he cut it into slices, I looked back up at the sky.
Eventually, I heard the clatter of a knife on the plate, signaling that he was done.
I turned back towards him, and was taken by surprise to see him on one knee.
That couldn't have been a comfortable position, I wonder why he was sitting like that.
"Melanie Attar, will you marry me?"
